---
import ConditionPage from '../../components/ConditionPage.astro';
---
<ConditionPage
	title="Treatment in Clapham"
	highlight="Running Injuries"
	heroSubtitle="Running injuries are common — especially when your training load builds faster than your body can adapt. Get back on your feet and back out running."
	breadcrumb="Running Injuries"
	seoTitle="Running Injuries Treatment in Clapham"
	seoDescription="Expert running injury treatment in Clapham, London. Strength, gait analysis, loading programmes and our Alter-G treadmill to get you running pain free."
	intro={[
		"Running injuries are common — especially when your training load builds faster than your body can adapt. We focus on understanding what's actually causing your injury rather than just managing pain.",
		"Whether you're training for a marathon or just getting started, we'll address the strength, technique and training factors that got you here, and build a plan to get you back out running.",
	]}
	symptomsHeading="When to get it"
	symptomsHighlight="checked"
	symptomsIntro="It's worth coming in for an assessment if you're experiencing any of the following:"
	symptomsList={[
		"Pain around the kneecap (runner's knee), especially on hills or stairs",
		"Stiffness or pain in the Achilles, particularly in the morning",
		"Shin pain during or after running",
		"Sharp heel pain (plantar fasciitis), especially at the start of a run",
		"Pain on the outside of the knee (IT band syndrome)",
		"Localised deep pain that worsens with impact",
	]}
	treatmentHeading="How we treat"
	treatmentHighlight="running injuries"
	treatmentIntro="Your treatment plan is built around your specific presentation and may include:"
	treatmentList={[
		"Physiotherapy to improve strength and control",
		"Manual therapy to reduce pain and stiffness",
		"Structured loading programme to rebuild tissue capacity",
		"Running technique advice and gait analysis",
		"Training, footwear, and return-to-running guidance",
		"Alter-G machine to maintain cardiovascular fitness",
	]}
	whoHeading="Who we"
	whoHighlight="help"
	whoList={[
		"Marathon and long-distance runners",
		"Parkrun and recreational runners",
		"Beginners building up to 5K",
		"Triathletes managing run-specific issues",
		"Track and performance athletes",
	]}
	faqs={[
		{ q: "Can I keep running while injured?", a: "In many cases, yes. We have an Alter G machine that helps massively with this." },
		{ q: "Do I need new running shoes?", a: "Not always. We\\'ll assess your current footwear and running style before recommending changes." },
		{ q: "What is gait analysis?", a: "We look at how you run to identify movement patterns that may be contributing to your pain." },
		{ q: "What is a loading programme?", a: "A structured set of exercises that gradually builds strength so your body can tolerate running." },
		{ q: "Can you help me prepare for a race?", a: "Yes — we can identify potential issues early and help you train more safely." },
	]}
/>
